        {
          "id": "tmmbq17y6tg41t",
          "text": "Math learning",
          "startTime": "22:30",
          "duration": "1h",
          "plannedIds": [],
          "notes": "**Martingales**: a mathematical model of a \"fair game.\" A sequence of random variables $X_1, X_2, \\dots, X_n$ is a martingale if the expected value of the next observation, given all the past observations, is exactly equal to the most recent observation:$E[X_{n+1} | X_1, X_2, \\dots, X_n] = X_n$，想象多轮抛硬币赌钱就是了\n\n**Optional Stopping Theorem (OST)**: If $M_n$ is a martingale and $\\tau$ is a valid stopping time (a rule for stopping that only depends on the present and past, not the future), then under certain bounded conditions:$$E[M_\\tau] = E[M_0]$$\n\n这里stopping time不是constant. 举例，如果我有100块，停止条件是赢到150或者输光，这两种结局的期望仍然是100，所以是p * 150 + (1 - p) * 0 = 100\n\n还看了下水印的实现方法 (a hash value depending on the previous context)",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-04T07:34:36.414Z"
        }
      ],
